{"cursor":"2443","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Single\n| Name = Closer Cover = Jars Of Clay - Closer.jpg Artist = Jars of Clay from\n| Album = Closer EP Released = 8 July 2008 Format = CD Digital download\n| Recorded = 2008 Genre = Rock, Synthpop Length = 3:39 (Closer EP\n| version) 3:56 (The Long Fall Back to Earth\n| version) Label = Gray Matters/Essential Producer = Jars of Clay & Ron\n| Aniello Last single = \"There Is a River\" (2007) This single =\n| \"'Closer'\" (2008) Next single = \"Two Hands\" (2009)\n}}\n\n\"'Closer'\" is a song written and performed by Christian rock act Jars of Clay.\nThe radio single was released in promotion of the band's 2008-released EP,\n[[Closer EP|Closer]]. Although the track also appears on the band's 2009 album\n[[The Long Fall Back to Earth]], the single was released far in advance of its\nannouncement and release to be considered that album's first single. The version\nof the song that appears on The Long Fall Back to Earth is a different mix than\nthe one that appears on the Closer EP, containing a longer intro and song\nlength. \"Closer\" was co-produced by Ron Aniello, who also helped co-produce the\nband's 2003 release [[Who We Are Instead]] and helped co-write a handful of\ntracks from their [[Good Monsters]] studio album.\n","linknr":164,"url":"Closer_(Jars_of_Clay_song)","recorded":1363418879,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Closer_(Jars_of_Clay_song)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Closer_(Jars_of_Clay_song)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7C